INTRAPANCREATIC
COMPRESSION
OF
THE
COMMON
BILE
DUCT
IN
CYSTIC
FIBROSIS
WE
REPORT
AN
INFANT
WITH
CYSTIC
FIBROSIS
PRESENTING
AT
BIRTH
WITH
MECONIUM
ILEUS
WHO
DEVELOPED
PROLONGED
CHOLESTATIC
JAUNDICE
FROM
COMPRESSION
OF
THE
COMMON
BILE
DUCT
AND
THE
PANCREATIC
DUCT
BY
ADVANCED
PANCREATIC
FIBROSIS
EXTRAHEPATIC
BILIARY
OBSTRUCTION
OF
THIS
NATURE
HAS
NOT
BEEN
PREVIOUSLY
DESCRIBED
IN
CYSTIC
FIBROSIS
